Location: Hyderabad

Recipe:
step1: Mix Marinade in a large pot . 
step2:Add chicken and coat well. 
step3:Marinade 20 minutes to overnight.
PAR BOILED RICE:
step4:Bring 3 litres / 3 quarts water to the boil, add salt and spices.
step5:Add rice, bring back up to the boil then cook for 4 minutes, or until rice is just cooked still a bit firm in the middle. 
BIRYANI:
step6:Place pot with chicken in it onto a stove over medium heat. Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
step7:Remove lid. Cook for 5 minutes, turning chicken twice.
step8:Remove from heat.
step9:Turn chicken so skin side is down - it should cover most of the base of the pot.
step10:Scatter over half the onion then half the coriander.
step11:Top with all the rice. Gently pat down and flatten surface.
step12:Drizzle saffron across rice surface in random pattern, then drizzle over ghee.
step13:Place lid on. Return to stove over medium heat.
step14:As soon as you see steam, turn down to low then cook for 25 minutes.
step15:Remove from stove, rest with lid on for 10 minutes
